        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 26 at 12:08PM EDT by NWS Grand Rapids MI</headline>
        <description>At 1208 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm
near Vicksburg, or 9 miles southeast of Portage, moving east at 30
mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Union City...          Burlington...          Fulton...
Athens...              Pine Creek...
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
